1
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,800
We are all Cinderella.

2
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:22,100
No matter what our size.

3
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:26,300
Within each one of us
there is a unique beauty and grace.

4
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:29,900
Finding that beauty, however, isn't easy.

5
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:35,100
See, Cinderella had to first recognize
that her problem wasn't her evil stepmother.

6
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:38,900
Her problem was that it was easier
to hide out, cleaning the house

7
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,100
than it was to go out
and find happiness.

8
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:44,400
She needed a fairy godmother

9
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:47,200
to empower her with the kind
of self confidence it takes

10
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:51,600
to reject the insecurity brought
on by unrealistic, overachieving,

11
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:54,400
airbrushed, anorexic
princess images in the media.

12
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:24,300
It took some very large
ovaries for Cinderella

13
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:29,600
to make a change to trade in her scrub brush
for a fabulous pair of dancing shoes.

14
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:35,500
But boy, was it worth it.

15
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:05,600
I'm gonna be so late.

16
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:17,000
No! I'm so late! Not today!

17
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:17,600
You okay?

18
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:24,600
Yeah. It's Pumpkin, my car...
Broke down. Thank you.

19
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:25,700
You named you car "Pumpkin"?

20
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:32,500
Yeah, she's a 65 Mustang restored.
You know kind of a...

21
00:02:32,540 --> 00:02:36,500
pumpkin-into-a-coach...
kind of thing.

22
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:38,900
I'm at Shine. Do you work here?

23
00:02:38,940 --> 00:02:41,400
It's just parttime. You?

24
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:46,500
Yeah. Until I get fired
for being late to a meeting!

25
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,400
Thank you!

26
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:52,600
Joy, I'm late.

27
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:54,900
The meeting's already started.
Lori's having a stroke.

28
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:55,900
Oh, my God.

29
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,200
Nice of you to join us this morning.

30
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:03,700
Lory, my car died and...

31
00:03:05,300 --> 00:03:11,100
So, Nancy, tell me. Can they sue us?

32
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:14,200
People can sue for anything.
It's my job to stop them.

33
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:19,400
But let's be careful. The
names we throw around when we write an
article about "celebrity cougars".

34
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:21,500
She should be flattered.

35
00:03:21,540 --> 00:03:23,450
Okay, people, other ideas.

36
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:24,500
Fourty is the new twenty.

37
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:25,500
Foisty foreplay tips.

38
00:03:25,540 --> 00:03:27,500
Feel great naked workout.

39
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:32,000
Nola. We were talking
about ideas for November.

40
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:32,800
Yeah.

41
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:36,100
Come up with something that ties Belinda
Apple's book and her November column?

42
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,800
What book?

43
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:45,600
For those among you who couldn't
bother to get here on time,
Nola Devlin, I'll repeat myself.

44
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,700
Stan's and Publishing which
owns Shine and therefore me,

45
00:03:48,740 --> 00:03:51,400
wants to publish a book
on Belinda Apple's columns.

46
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:54,200
"Apple gets to the core" sort of...
a best-of self help book.

47
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:56,800
Belinda never mentioned
a book to me.

48
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:58,600
You edit her column.
You're not her best friend.

49
00:03:58,640 --> 00:04:00,800
I will be writing
the foreword to the book.

50
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:01,700
You?

51
00:04:01,740 --> 00:04:03,400
