233
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:34,600
Could we get that table by the window?
That's our favourite spot.

234
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:36,300
Oh, I'm really sorry.
That table's reserved.

235
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:39,400
Oh, really! I didn't know that
you could reserve tables.

236
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:41,900
Well, you can now.
We're under new management.

237
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:44,700
Chester... is it?

238
00:14:44,740 --> 00:14:47,500
Well, this is Nola Devlin.
She edits Belinda Apple's column

239
00:14:47,540 --> 00:14:49,500
which I'm sure everyone
in America has read.

240
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:55,600
It's just that, you know, the first saturday
of every month we sit at that table.

241
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:57,500
And this saturday it's reserved.

242
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:00,200
Oh, God, here we go.

243
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:03,000
You wouldn't, by any chance,
not be giving us that table

244
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,700
because we are
on the zaftig side. Would you?

245
00:15:04,740 --> 00:15:06,200
I don't know what you mean.

