00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:07,400
Because we're fat.

247
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:09,900
Would you like to order?

248
00:15:09,940 --> 00:15:13,800
Yes. We'd like the table by the window.

249
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:18,300
Ladies, if you're not happy with the
service here there are a number
of other restaurants is Princeton.

250
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:23,000
Zaftig? What are we? Russian peasant women?

251
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:24,600
This is fat discrimination.

252
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:26,200
Sorry!

253
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:36,100
I wish I had a magic wand so
I could instantly make us thin.

254
00:15:36,140 --> 00:15:40,300
Like Cinderella. Except instead of a
ball gown we've got hip bones and a waist.

255
00:15:40,340 --> 00:15:42,900
Sorry, my magic wand
is in the repair shop.

256
00:15:42,940 --> 00:15:46,200
Maybe it's time
for a fairy godmother.

257
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,800
Don't do it. Don't pull her out.

258
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:50,800
Belinda Apple represents the woman
I would be if I could...

259
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:54,000
reclaim my power and
get out of my own way.

260
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,600
We all need to do that.

261
00:15:55,640 --> 00:16:00,100
If Belinda is so great
at giving advice

262
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,700
then how come Nola works
for her and she's still such a mess?

263
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:01,000
Hey!

264
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:04,600
Honey, you're a fantastic writer
but you're editing someone else's work.

265
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:06,900
You're a wonderful woman but
there are no men in your life.

266
00:16:06,940 --> 00:16:09,200
And that pizza delivery guy...
not Prince Charming.

267
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:10,900
Come on now, listen.

268
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,500
Dear fabulous Belinda,

269
00:16:12,540 --> 00:16:15,400
I'm tired of being overweight,
bla bla bla,

270
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:19,000
I've dieted my whole life,
and now I'm almost 250 pounds.

271
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:20,400
What should I do?

272
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,400
Two fifty! Wow! She should
stop weighting herself.

273
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,700
Dear sexy underneath it all.

274
00:16:25,740 --> 00:16:29,600
I will let you in on my deepest,
darkest secret.

275
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:35,000
I used to be desperately overweight.
Finally I couldn't stand it any more.

276
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:38,300
I had to take control of my life.
Was it hard? Yes. How did I do it?

277
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:41,600
By reclaiming my power,
getting out of my own way,

278
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:45,200
by finding a symbol to remind myself
of the person I knew I was inside

279
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:47,600
and by being honest
with myself.

280
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:52,100
There's no way that woman was ever fat.

281
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,100
Let's say we follow
Belindas's example and just do it.

282
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:01,200
No, I can't, you guys. I have
way too much on my plate right now.

283
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:03,100
You're just scared of change.

284
00:17:03,140 --> 00:17:08,200
I like my life. I have a good job,
a husband who loves me

285
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:08,000
with whom I have sex once a month.
Why should I change?

286
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:09,300
But, are you happy?

287
00:17:09,340 --> 00:17:12,599
I mean, completely, utterly,
every moment happy.

288
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:19,500
I'm not. I mean... Paul loves me
but I don't love me.

289
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:25,000
Every spring we take the kids
to Paul's parents in Seattle.

290
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:28,100
Kids want to go some place warm
but we don't because they know

291
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:30,900
I would never step foot
on a beach on a bathing suit.

292
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:35,300
I just wanna be with my family
doing normal family things.

293
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:37,700
Oh, come on. Don't cry.

294
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:42,700
Let's do it. Let's do
what Belinda said

295
00:17:42,740 --> 00:17:45,500
and let's become the women
we know we are inside.

296
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,100
You really believe in her, don't you?

297
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:48,900
Don't you?

298
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:52,700
Don't you want the person inside
of you to finally emerge?

299
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,700
That's a complicated question.

300
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:55,800
We've all been on diet.

301
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:57,100
But this time we'll do it together.

302
00:17:57,140 --> 00:18:01,100
We're there for one another.
Totally honest and no one's off the hook.

303
00:18:01,140 --> 00:18:02,800
On one condition.

304
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:05,400
In four months we go back
to the Willoughbe Cafe,

305
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:07,500
we get that table
by the window and

306
00:18:07,540 --> 00:18:11,800
we shame Chester until
he is groveling at our feet.

307
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:12,700
Done.

308
00:18:12,740 --> 00:18:17,200
One, we meet September 5th
to humilliate Chester.

309
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:21,200
Supporting each other no matter
where and no matter what.

310
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:22,800
We can work out together
every other day.

311
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:24,200
To start.

312
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:31,000
Workout and diet. No secret stashes.
Nola, you know what I'm talking about.

313
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:34,800
And we need our symbols to remind us
of who we're gonna be.

314
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:42,700
Mine is red. When I was thin,
I wore color. Now I just...

315
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,700
well, I wear Eileen Fischer versions of a burka.

316
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:51,200
Nancy wants bold proud red and I...
wanna wear bikini on the beach.

317
00:18:51,300 --> 00:18:52,200
Nola?

318
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,400
I don't know. Can I think about it?

319
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:00,800
All right. Nola's goal TBD.
We have weekly weigh-ins with our weight-loss pact.

320
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,300
Can we call it something else?

321
00:19:03,300 --> 00:19:09,700
Well, since Belinda is our fairy godmother
how about "the Cinderella pact"?

322
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:12,900
A toast! To change.

323
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:16,900
To friendship.

324
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:20,400
To the Cinderella pact.

325
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:25,600
Belinda would be so proud of it.

326
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:28,700
I hope so. I really do.

327
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,400
I can't go in there.

328
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:43,900
"Can't" is not part
of our vocabulary, okay?

329
00:19:43,940 --> 00:19:48,000
Together we have strength.

330
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:49,000
We give each other confidence.

331
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:58,100
Honey, listen, nobody said
this was gonna be easy, right? We can...

332
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,700
We should hire a personal trainer.
Work out on our own terms.

333
00:20:00,740 --> 00:20:03,200
Great idea! What do you think of that?

334
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:04,200
Okay.

335
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:08,600
Nola? Hey, you work out here too?

336
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:10,300
No.

337
00:20:10,340 --> 00:20:14,100
No, because we already
worked out actually.

338
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:16,800
It was really intense.
We had a good one, right?

339
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:25,100
This is my friend Nancy and
this is my friend Deb.

340
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:28,600
This is Chip. He gave a ride
when Punpkin died.

341
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,200
Really!

342
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:37,900
I'm gonna go in. It was nice
meeting you, guys. Good to see you.

343
00:20:37,940 --> 00:20:39,400
Yeah!

344
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,600
Oh, my God. I'm such a looser.

345
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:43,900
He is adorable!

346
00:20:43,940 --> 00:20:47,900
Deb, don't get any ideas.
He is too adorable for me.

347
00:20:47,940 --> 00:20:50,100
Oh, come on. He would be lucky
to have you, wouldn't he?

348
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:51,000
Absolutely.

349
00:20:52,700 --> 00:20:54,100
Cinderella pact.

350
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:03,800
Well, that was exhausting.
I felt the burn.

351
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,400
Me too. I think I pulled
something back there.

352
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:07,500
Oh, great first day, ladies.

353
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:08,700
Keep it coming.
Let's go. Punch.

354
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,500
Final stretch, Deb.
How you doing?

355
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,100
Hangin' in.

356
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:12,400
All right.

357
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,400
Push it. Let's go.

358
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:15,900
Keep it tight,
keep it tight.

359
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,500
Okay, 45 seconds.

360
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:19,900
Come on, Deb.
Let's go!

361
00:21:26,900 --> 00:21:29,500
Oh, my God!
What do you guys eat for breakfast?

362
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:13,300
Oh, Deb, they're waiting!
Let's go Deb!

363
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:20,100
Go, Deb!

364
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:20,900
Yeah!

365
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:29,800
That's it.
That's my goal.

366
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,100
Oh, Nola, it's...

367
00:22:31,140 --> 00:22:32,200
Perfect.

368
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:34,100
Cincerella would be proud.

369
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,500
Hello!

370
00:22:50,540 --> 00:22:52,300
Belinda, it's Charlotte,
your agent,

371
00:22:52,340 --> 00:22:53,400
who you never call back.

372
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:55,800
Hi, Charlotte.
How are you, darling?

373
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:58,400
I'm sorry to call you
so late. But we really need

374
00:22:58,440 --> 00:22:59,300
to talk about this book.

375
00:22:59,340 --> 00:23:02,700
I've been getting calls from
a Lory Digrigio at Stanson.

376
00:23:02,740 --> 00:23:03,900
Over twenty, to be exact.

377
00:23:03,940 --> 00:23:06,400
She really needs to
schedule personal appearences

378
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:08,500
and a promotional tour
to launch this book.

379
00:23:08,540 --> 00:23:11,600
It's part of your contract.
They really need some dates.

380
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:15,000
Do you know what?
I will check my calendar

381
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:18,500
and I will get back to you
with many options, okay?

382
00:23:18,540 --> 00:23:20,700
No, no, Belinda.
It would be really helpful

383
00:23:20,740 --> 00:23:22,600
if we could do this right now
while I got you on the phone...

384
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:26,900
This is... Charlotte, I have to call
you back. It's a terrible line! Bye! Bad line!

385
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,800
Oh! No!

386
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:47,600
Mr. Tuchman, everything's under
control. I just burned my dinner again.

387
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:50,100
Hi!

388
00:23:50,140 --> 00:23:51,400
What happened?

389
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:55,600
I'm sorry. I set off the smoke alarm
again. It happens all the time.

390
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:59,200
Don't worry about a thing. There.

391
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:00,500
What's up?

392
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:04,000
I brought over something
I want you to watch.

393
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:05,400
Okay.

394
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:12,800
Gastric bypass.
Miracle answer or helpful tool.

395
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:16,500
Once you get past the black stools
and the possible death thing

396
00:24:16,540 --> 00:24:19,600
it's actually pretty okay.

397
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:23,100
Deb, you can't be serious
about having this surgery.

398
00:24:26,500 --> 00:24:31,000
Mr. Tuchman, everything's
under control. See? It stopped.

399
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:32,600
Don't hang up. It's Chip.

400
00:24:35,300 --> 00:24:36,600
Chip? How did you get this number?

401
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:39,700
The company directory.

402
00:24:39,740 --> 00:24:43,600
Oh, did I leave something
in your track?

403
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,800
No, I was actually
in your neighbourhood

404
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:47,100
and was wandering if
you wanna meet for a drink.

405
00:24:48,500 --> 00:24:50,600
Meet for a drink?
Meet tonight?

406
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:51,800
Yes! Yes!

407
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:53,900
Could you hold on
for a second, please?

408
00:24:53,940 --> 00:24:57,000
I wanna talk to you
about this surgery.

409
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:59,400
I'm not having it tomorrow.
Are you nuts?

410
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:02,100
Stomach surgery DVD or
amazingly hunky guy?

411
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:04,300
All right. I got it.

412
00:25:06,100 --> 00:25:09,200
Yeah, I think I could
probably make it.

413
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:11,400
Where are you?

414
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:14,100
Brown's? In half hour?

415
00:25:14,140 --> 00:25:15,300
Tell him you'll be there.

416
00:25:15,340 --> 00:25:17,500
Half hour. I'll be there.

417
00:25:17,540 --> 00:25:19,800
All right. Bye.

418
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:22,600
Oh, my God.

419
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:25,500
Don't just stand there. Let's get you dressed.
Come on.

420
00:25:25,540 --> 00:25:27,900
Half an hour! What am I?
Wonder Woman? Look at me!

421
00:25:27,940 --> 00:25:29,800
But you've got four hands!
Come on!

422
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:39,200
Nola...

423
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:40,200
Hi!

424
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:43,500
I kind of feel really overdressed

425
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:48,300
Excuse me. The lady will have...

426
00:25:48,340 --> 00:25:50,500
A white wine spritzer.

427
00:25:51,300 --> 00:25:53,100
Thank you.
Right over here.

428
00:25:53,140 --> 00:25:57,600
Whoa. It is a good thing I changed.
I was gonna wear the exact same outfit.

429
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,900
- You look nice.
- Thank you.

430
00:26:01,940 --> 00:26:03,400
So, did you buy a new car yet?

431
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:05,500
I rented one. A Volvo.

432
00:26:05,540 --> 00:26:07,400
- Very safe choice.
- Yeah.

433
00:26:07,700 --> 00:26:10,200
But safe is not all it's cracked up to be.
Sometimes you need to step

434
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:12,700
outside your confort zone
and take risks to be successful.

435
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:14,500
Okay.

436
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:19,800
Another one-sided conversation I've been
having with my father for years.

437
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:27,500
So, what's his definition of success?

438
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:31,100
Someone who is hard-working,
responsible and focused.

439
00:26:31,140 --> 00:26:35,200
So, you're lazy, reckless and unfocused?

440
00:26:36,300 --> 00:26:39,500
That's the old me.
Apparently I was avoiding success.

441
00:26:39,540 --> 00:26:42,400
It sounds to me like you might've
been avoiding failure.

442
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:45,000
Not a bad life strategy, you know.
You never try, you never fail.

443
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:49,700
Probably. It's a very
astute observation.

444
00:26:49,740 --> 00:26:50,700
Yes, well...

445
00:26:50,740 --> 00:26:54,500
I'm very insightful and intuitive.
It's a gift and a curse.

446
00:26:54,540 --> 00:26:55,200
Really?

447
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,100
Yeah.

448
00:26:56,140 --> 00:26:58,600
What am I thinking right now?

449
00:27:01,300 --> 00:27:03,600
You're thinking that you
don't wanna tell me

450
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:05,800
all your secrets 'cause it'll
make you seem vulnerable.

451
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,200
You're right.

452
00:27:13,500 --> 00:27:15,500
Never talk about my personal life.

453
00:27:17,300 --> 00:27:19,100
All right. I'm gonna do
something for you here, okay?

454
00:27:19,140 --> 00:27:21,000
I'm gonna tell you one
embarasing thing about me

455
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:23,700
so that we can be equally
vulnerable.

456
00:27:23,740 --> 00:27:25,400
That's only fair.

457
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:32,200
I'm a criminal. I downloaded a movie
ilegally off the Internet

458
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,500
before it came out on DVD.

459
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:35,600
So, you're in the run
from the law.

460
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:37,200
Yes, you're aiding
and abetting a criminal.

461
00:27:40,900 --> 00:27:41,800
Damn.

462
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:42,600
What?

463
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:44,600
That woman's just walked out
of the ladies' room.

464
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:47,900
She's sort of an old girlfriend.
Things ended badly.

465
00:27:49,300 --> 00:27:54,700
Ended badly like
"she went to yoga and never came back" badly
or "she boiled your pet rabbit" badly.

466
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,200
Go with me on this.

467
00:28:02,100 --> 00:28:04,400
Well, hello.
I thought you died.

468
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:08,600
Not dead. Just travelling,
busy with work and...

469
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:10,200
This is my girlfriend, Nola.

470
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:12,900
Nola?

471
00:28:12,940 --> 00:28:16,600
Nola... Devlin. Hi!
I'm his girlfriend.

472
00:28:16,640 --> 00:28:19,800
You are beyond pathetic.

473
00:28:19,700 --> 00:28:23,600
You stopped calling me
because you're dating this fat lady?

474
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:27,100
No, I stopped calling you
because we broke up six months ago.

475
00:28:27,140 --> 00:28:28,300
We're over.

476
00:28:28,340 --> 00:28:31,000
We're not over... until she sings.

477
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:32,200
You know what?

478
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,200
Hey!

479
00:28:39,100 --> 00:28:40,500
Classy, Ange. Thanks.

480
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:44,500
Nola, wait up!

481
00:28:44,540 --> 00:28:45,400
No, no, no!

482
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:48,500
I'm so sorry.
Angie is a total psyco. I...

483
00:28:48,540 --> 00:28:51,000
Please, can I at least walk you home?

484
00:28:51,040 --> 00:28:52,800
No, obviously I can take care of myself.

485
00:28:52,840 --> 00:28:57,300
What if I just walk six steps behind you?
Then if I get mugged you can step in and save me.

486
00:28:58,700 --> 00:29:05,200
I'm an idiot, okay? I got caught off-guard.
I had no idea that she'd be there.

487
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:05,200
I never should've used you
like that. I'm sorry.

488
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:06,400
You know, you should be sorry.

489
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:08,400
Don't you get it?

490
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:13,300
Girls like me are easy targets for
girls like that, you know?

491
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:16,900
You should never have put me
in that position.

492
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:22,000
It was humiliating for me. And
