00:56:38,200 --> 00:56:39,400
I know you.

983
00:56:39,440 --> 00:56:40,000
I love you.

984
00:56:40,040 --> 00:56:41,800
And you will do the right thing.

985
00:56:43,500 --> 00:56:44,600
Yeah.

986
00:56:44,640 --> 00:56:47,000
You know, one good thing
has come out of all of this.

987
00:56:47,040 --> 00:56:48,100
What?

988
00:56:48,140 --> 00:56:51,400
The Cinderella pact.
You look amazing.

989
00:56:51,440 --> 00:56:53,500
Yeah, I've lost another five pounds.

990
00:56:53,540 --> 00:56:54,900
Oh, god. Nancy,

991
00:56:54,940 --> 00:56:57,200
how am I going to get out
of this in one piece?

992
00:56:57,500 --> 00:56:58,800
Lori's coming apart at the seams.

993
00:56:58,840 --> 00:57:02,700
I mean, she's got this contract she wants
Belinda to sign. You know? she's crazy!

994
00:57:02,740 --> 00:57:05,800
And I can't keep
stalling her for very much longer.

995
00:57:05,840 --> 00:57:07,400
Come on. we're going to figure this out.

996
00:57:09,200 --> 00:57:10,500
It's Deb.

997
00:57:10,540 --> 00:57:11,700
- Where?
- Shh.

998
00:57:12,400 --> 00:57:13,400
Hey, Deb.

999
00:57:15,300 --> 00:57:18,500
Hey. Deb, where are you?

1000
00:57:19,700 --> 00:57:20,600
If anything, scotch makes you happy.

1001
00:57:20,640 --> 00:57:24,000
Hey, guys! this is josh.

1002
00:57:24,500 --> 00:57:26,400
Josh, these ar the friends
I was telling you about.

1003
00:57:26,440 --> 00:57:27,500
Do you want a drink?

1004
00:57:28,900 --> 00:57:30,600
No. No, I think we're good.

1005
00:57:30,640 --> 00:57:32,800
I thought you weren't supposed
to drink after your surgery?

1006
00:57:32,840 --> 00:57:34,000
Who're you, her mother?

1007
00:57:35,200 --> 00:57:36,700
No, josh. Her best friend.

1008
00:57:36,740 --> 00:57:38,700
Come on.

1009
00:57:41,600 --> 00:57:43,000
Do you mind telling us
what you think you're doing?

1010
00:57:43,040 --> 00:57:46,200
I was just having some fun.
Is that a crime?

1011
00:57:46,800 --> 00:57:50,600
Okay, "fun" is a pedicure.
"Fun" is... is a great day at the beach.

1012
00:57:50,640 --> 00:57:51,900
A fast car is "fun"...

1013
00:57:51,940 --> 00:57:54,700
not knocking back manhattans
with some random businessman.

1014
00:57:54,740 --> 00:57:55,900
You're married!

1015
00:57:55,940 --> 00:58:00,400
I know. I've been settling my whole life.
I don't want to settle anymore.

1016
00:58:00,440 --> 00:58:05,700
You know, it's terrifying,
but for the first time ever,

1017
00:58:05,700 --> 00:58:10,400
I feel like I have choices.
And ain't that why I went through the surgery?

1018
00:58:11,100 --> 00:58:11,900
Do you know what I did today?

1019
00:58:11,940 --> 00:58:16,200
I went to an assembly at my son's
school. I was so happy being there,

1020
00:58:16,240 --> 00:58:20,700
just a mom sitting in the audience,
not some fat woman everyone was staring at.

1021
00:58:20,740 --> 00:58:22,900
Paul never showed.

1022
00:58:22,940 --> 00:58:26,600
Do you know why I married him?

1023
00:58:26,640 --> 00:58:29,500
Because I was scared
no one else would have me.

1024
00:58:29,540 --> 00:58:31,700
You know what's worse?
He knew that!

1025
00:58:31,740 --> 00:58:34,700
I mean, he doesn't love me,
he just wants to control me.

1026
00:58:34,740 --> 00:58:36,500
Are you going to leave him?

1027
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:39,500
I don't know.

1028
00:58:39,540 --> 00:58:41,900
What would Belinda say?

1029
00:58:43,000 --> 00:58:46,500
Yeah. what would Belinda say?

1030
00:58:51,200 --> 00:58:56,700
I think she'd tell you that you deserve
better than trolling in bars for
attention from strange men.

1031
00:58:56,740 --> 00:58:59,700
You are better.
And you know what?

1032
00:58:59,740 --> 00:59:02,000
You should create the life you deserve.

1033
00:59:03,900 --> 00:59:05,500
That's exactly what she'd say.

1034
00:59:05,540 --> 00:59:06,700
Yeah, no joke.

1035
00:59:08,800 --> 00:59:09,900
Tell her.

1036
00:59:11,600 --> 00:59:12,100
What?

1037
00:59:15,500 --> 00:59:18,100
She is Belinda.

1038
00:59:20,000 --> 00:59:21,200
That's impossible.

1039
00:59:24,100 --> 00:59:25,100
You're Belinda?

1040
00:59:26,600 --> 00:59:28,400
I'm Belinda.

1041
00:59:31,800 --> 00:59:32,800
But how?

1042
00:59:32,840 --> 00:59:35,600
It's really complicated.
I mean...

1043
00:59:36,800 --> 00:59:39,600
well, I started by submitting
my columns electronically to Lori.

1044
00:59:39,500 --> 00:59:41,900
Do you mean all the advice
I got from Belinda,

1045
00:59:43,000 --> 00:59:47,700
the advice that I changed my life for,
the Cinderella pact, that was all a lie?

1046
00:59:47,740 --> 00:59:51,500
No. no! I-I believed every word.

1047
00:59:51,540 --> 00:59:55,000
It just... it seemed like you
would listen to it more

1048
00:59:55,040 --> 00:59:56,800
when it came from someone like Belinda.

1049
00:59:56,840 --> 00:59:58,800
I just want what's best for you.

1050
00:59:58,700 --> 01:00:01,600
And to regain my power
and be the person I am inside.

1051
01:00:01,640 --> 01:00:03,500
Yes! yes! yes!

1052
01:00:03,540 --> 01:00:06,500
That was part of the pact,
and we were supposed to be honest

1053
01:00:06,540 --> 01:00:08,500
We would always be honest
with one another,

1054
01:00:10,500 --> 01:00:12,200
and you were lying from the start.

1055
01:00:12,240 --> 01:00:15,000
You never believed any of this could be real.

1056
01:00:15,040 --> 01:00:19,100
That's not true.
I hoped it would be. I did.

1057
01:00:21,500 --> 01:00:24,600
Losing weight has given me
the confidence to stand up

1058
01:00:24,640 --> 01:00:26,000
for myself and be honest about my feelings.

1059
01:00:28,300 --> 01:00:30,400
You have no idea how much you hurt me.

1060
01:00:34,300 --> 01:00:37,000
Well, I don't want to deal with this right now.

1061
01:00:37,040 --> 01:00:38,700
I can't.

1062
01:00:40,400 --> 01:00:41,800
I'll go.

1063
01:00:47,900 --> 01:00:50,800
Nola, hi. Sorry about
leaving a message. Again.

1064
01:00:51,700 --> 01:00:52,900
Since I haven't heard from you,

1065
01:00:52,940 --> 01:00:56,800
you are either, "a" on a road trip with
Otis and too busy to check your messages,

1066
01:00:56,840 --> 01:01:00,000
or "b" in the finals of an
international croquet tournament,

1067
01:01:00,040 --> 01:01:04,100
and unaware you have messages, or...
"c" avoiding me and hoping I stop calling.

1068
01:01:04,140 --> 01:01:07,700
I vote for "a" or "b",
because "c" makes me sad.

1069
01:01:18,600 --> 01:01:21,400
Yes, hello, is charlotte there?

1070
01:01:22,800 --> 01:01:24,600
This is her client, Belinda Apple.

1071
01:01:26,000 --> 01:01:30,200
Could you let her know that I need her
to call me as soon as possible, please?

1072
01:01:31,100 --> 01:01:32,200
Thank you.

1073
01:01:57,400 --> 01:01:58,100
Charlotte?

1074
01:01:58,140 --> 01:01:59,300
Yes?

1075
01:02:00,900 --> 01:02:03,200
I'm Nola Devlin, Belinda Apple's editor.

1076
01:02:03,240 --> 01:02:04,300
Where is she?

1077
01:02:04,340 --> 01:02:06,300
Actually, you're looking right at her.

1078
01:02:06,340 --> 01:02:07,600
I'm Belinda Apple.

1079
01:02:09,000 --> 01:02:11,400
Of course you are, darling.
There's a little bit of "Belinda" in all of us.

1080
01:02:11,600 --> 01:02:12,600
No, charlotte.

1081
01:02:12,640 --> 01:02:15,400
I'm your client.
I'm Belinda Apple.

1082
01:02:17,100 --> 01:02:23,100
But you're so not-british, or stylish.
No-- no offense.

1083
01:02:25,100 --> 01:02:27,700
I thought you'd be younger, but then,

1084
01:02:27,740 --> 01:02:31,200
maturity is just experience
wrapped in wrinkles, isn't it?

1085
01:02:31,600 --> 01:02:35,000
Oh, my god. You really are Belinda.

1086
01:02:35,600 --> 01:02:39,700
Correction-- I've been pretending to be her,
and I've hurt the people I love the most.

1087
01:02:39,740 --> 01:02:42,600
My whole life is a monumental trainwreck.

1088
01:02:42,640 --> 01:02:44,300
I'm probably going to get fired, go to jail,

1089
01:02:44,340 --> 01:02:47,100
and never work as a journalist again,
and I was just wondering if you could help me.

1090
01:02:47,600 --> 01:02:49,900
Oh, lord, let's get you a drink.

1091
01:02:51,500 --> 01:02:54,400
Wow, you have got yourself into quite the quandary.

1092
01:02:55,000 --> 01:02:57,900
I know, and I can't fake it anymore.
I can't.

1093
01:02:57,940 --> 01:03:03,600
You can fake a lot of things,
but you cannot fake talent,
whether you call yourself Belinda or Nina...

1094
01:03:03,640 --> 01:03:04,400
Nola.

1095
01:03:04,440 --> 01:03:09,200
Whatever. You are a writer.
Believe in that. Women love your column.

1096
01:03:09,240 --> 01:03:11,400
I have the fan mail to prove it.

1097
01:03:11,440 --> 01:03:14,600
Fan mail is not going
to keep me out of jail.

1098
01:03:14,640 --> 01:03:17,000
Okay, then. okay, then.

1099
01:03:17,040 --> 01:03:21,100
You do have some options.
One: do nothing.

1100
01:03:21,140 --> 01:03:22,800
Let the chips fall where they may.

1101
01:03:22,840 --> 01:03:27,900
Two: write a letter of resignation,
quit before the whole thing falls apart.

1102
01:03:29,600 --> 01:03:31,000
But your legal problems won't go away.

1103
01:03:32,900 --> 01:03:36,800
Or three: show up, tell the truth,
and watch the whole thing implode in person.

1104
01:03:38,000 --> 01:03:38,900
It's perfect.

1105
01:03:38,940 --> 01:03:41,600
Well, not the imploding part, of course, but

1106
01:03:41,640 --> 01:03:44,000
why shouldn't you go to that party?

1107
01:03:44,000 --> 01:03:47,500
Um, here's a clue: I'm not Belinda Apple.

1108
01:03:47,800 --> 01:03:50,700
Not yet. But with a litte work...

1109
01:03:51,800 --> 01:03:53,400
I think you could bring her to life.

1110
01:03:55,000 --> 01:03:55,700
You're crazy.

1111
01:03:55,740 --> 01:03:58,000
Yeah, "crazy" is sometimes the basis of genius.

1112
01:04:00,300 --> 01:04:02,200
Go as Belinda.

1113
01:04:02,240 --> 01:04:07,100
You keep your secret, I keep my commission.
It's a win-win situation.

1114
01:04:07,140 --> 01:04:11,100
Nobody is ever going to believe
that I'm Belinda Apple.

1115
01:04:12,100 --> 01:04:13,200
Think about it.

1116
01:04:23,200 --> 01:04:24,800
Nola?

1117
01:04:24,840 --> 01:04:28,400
Hmm? Chip! Alex...
whoever you are.

1118
01:04:28,440 --> 01:04:29,900
What are you doing here?

1119
01:04:31,100 --> 01:04:34,400
Um, I was supposed to meet
Belinda Apple's literary agent

1120
01:04:34,440 --> 01:04:37,000
but I just got a message
saying she had to cancel.

1121
01:04:39,900 --> 01:04:41,000
Have you eaten dinner?

1122
01:04:41,040 --> 01:04:44,400
Haven't eaten lunch and...
this is dinner. Mm!

1123
01:04:46,000 --> 01:04:49,900
Wow. It looks like your Cinderella
diet's a little extreme.

1124
01:04:49,940 --> 01:04:50,400
"Cinderella pact"

1125
01:04:50,440 --> 01:04:51,400
Right.

1126
01:04:51,440 --> 01:04:53,000
And you have no idea how extreme.

1127
01:04:53,040 --> 01:04:55,500
It kinda messes with your head, you know?

1128
01:04:56,400 --> 01:05:00,000
I don't, but I know
you need some food, real food,

1129
01:05:00,040 --> 01:05:03,300
and since it looks like
you've lost even more weight,

1130
01:05:03,340 --> 01:05:05,000
I think you could afford
to eat something.

1131
01:05:05,040 --> 01:05:05,600
Thank you.

1132
01:05:07,700 --> 01:05:08,500
Sorry I lied.

1133
01:05:08,540 --> 01:05:12,200
Okay, listen. you lie, I lie,
everybody lies.

1134
01:05:12,240 --> 01:05:16,000
We all tell little lies,
and big lies, and middle-of-the-road lies.

1135
01:05:16,900 --> 01:05:18,000
We're not to be trusted.

1136
01:05:19,400 --> 01:05:21,600
Cheaters never prosper. Or is it liars?
Gosh, I can never remember.

1137
01:05:22,500 --> 01:05:26,700
Go home... Alex Stanson.

1138
01:05:26,740 --> 01:05:29,400
I don't want to go home.

1139
01:05:30,800 --> 01:05:32,900
You're a nice guy.

1140
01:05:32,940 --> 01:05:37,100
You're a really, really nice guy.
You're too nice for me.

1141
01:05:37,140 --> 01:05:38,400
That's not true.

1142
01:05:41,000 --> 01:05:46,900
You don't know the real Nola Devlin,
the inner-workings, the heart and soul.

1143
01:05:46,940 --> 01:05:55,700
Here's what I do know. Nola Devlin
is funny, smart, pretty.

1144
01:05:57,000 --> 01:05:59,500
See?
Too nice.

1145
01:05:59,540 --> 01:06:02,200
I like who I am with you.

1146
01:06:02,240 --> 01:06:08,400
I'm not who you think I am.
I mean, I am, I am, but I'm not.

1147
01:06:09,600 --> 01:06:10,900
Don't we all feel that way?

1148
01:06:10,940 --> 01:06:13,100
Oh, listen, I'm serious.
There is no...

1149
01:06:19,100 --> 01:06:20,300
Very nice.

1150
01:06:23,200 --> 01:06:25,000
Did I just say that out loud?

1151
01:06:25,040 --> 01:06:25,800
No.

1152
01:06:33,600 --> 01:06:34,300
Oh, sorry.

1153
01:06:42,500 --> 01:06:43,100
Wait.

1154
01:06:43,700 --> 01:06:48,100
I-I'm not like other girls you've been with,
so I just wanted you to...

1155
01:06:48,140 --> 01:06:48,800
Thank god.

1156
01:06:52,700 --> 01:06:55,800
No, it's just that...
See. My body is...

1157
01:06:55,600 --> 01:06:56,400
Beautiful.

1158
01:06:57,900 --> 01:06:59,600
You have a beautiful body.

1159
01:07:10,300 --> 01:07:12,900
Let's never leave here, ever.

1160
01:07:15,200 --> 01:07:18,700
Oh, god. Let me guess.
Taiwan for six weeks.

1161
01:07:20,200 --> 01:07:25,100
No. Actually L.A. for a shareholder's
meeting, and then back here friday for
the book launch.

1162
01:07:26,300 --> 01:07:28,600
Alex, about the book launch...

1163
01:07:30,700 --> 01:07:36,000
What if Belinda doesn't show?
I mean, she can be really unreliable.

1164
01:07:37,700 --> 01:07:43,600
Well, if she doesn't show
she'll be letting down a lot of people.

1165
01:07:45,000 --> 01:07:46,400
I'm sure it would be
disappointing for you,

1166
01:07:46,440 --> 01:07:48,700
since you're as much a part
of the book as Belinda is.

1167
01:07:50,900 --> 01:07:51,800
- Look, Alex, I...
- Nola,

1168
01:07:51,840 --> 01:07:53,900
I think I'm falling in love with you.

1169
01:08:10,100 --> 01:08:12,200
Chip? A-Alex?

1170
01:08:13,600 --> 01:08:16,100
- Hey.
- Hi.

1171
01:08:16,140 --> 01:08:17,200
Good morning.

1172
01:08:20,300 --> 01:08:22,800
I have to catch my flight. Go back to sleep.

1173
01:08:24,000 --> 01:08:25,700
I'll see you at the book launch.

1174
01:08:26,600 --> 01:08:27,500
All right.

1175
01:08:27,540 --> 01:08:28,399
Get some rest.

1176
01:08:28,439 --> 01:08:29,200
Okay.

1177
01:08:34,600 --> 01:08:35,300
Bye.

1178
01:08:39,500 --> 01:08:40,600
Wait.

1179
01:08:40,640 --> 01:08:45,500
There is no Belinda Apple,
and I'm a big fat liar.

1180
01:09:12,000 --> 01:09:14,200
Hey, Nola! whatcha doing?

1181
01:09:14,240 --> 01:09:17,600
Hey, joy, have you seen Lori?

1182
01:09:17,640 --> 01:09:19,399
She's getting her dress
fitted for the party.

1183
01:09:20,100 --> 01:09:22,130
Oh, but, hey, if you see her,

1184
01:09:22,170 --> 01:09:26,000
can you tell her that Belinda's agent
sent over a ton of fan mail
from her office last night?

1185
01:09:27,000 --> 01:09:28,399
Fan mail?

1186
01:09:28,439 --> 01:09:30,100
Well, it is in the mailroom.

1187
01:09:31,700 --> 01:09:33,000
Thanks, joy.

1188
01:09:48,700 --> 01:09:52,800
Dear Belinda,
you saved my life! I was 216...

1189
01:09:52,840 --> 01:09:55,900
Dear Belinda, thank you,
thank you, thank you.

1190
01:09:58,000 --> 01:10:02,500
Belinda, you are my guardian angel.
You inspired me to follow my dreams.

1191
01:10:02,400 --> 01:10:06,200
Dear Miss Apple, if it weren't for you,
I wouldn't be here writing this letter.

1192
01:10:15,000 --> 01:10:16,000
Hey, Nance.

1193
01:10:16,040 --> 01:10:17,200
Hey. You ready for tomorrow?

1194
01:10:17,240 --> 01:10:18,800
What's tomorrow?

1195
01:10:18,500 --> 01:10:19,200
Oh, it's end-game.

1196
01:10:19,240 --> 01:10:23,000
The day we go back to the Willoughby cafe
and witness some serious grovelling?

1197
01:10:23,900 --> 01:10:26,500
Right. Right. God.

1198
01:10:27,700 --> 01:10:31,500
My dress is gone.

1199
01:10:32,700 --> 01:10:33,400
Your goal dress?

1200
01:10:35,800 --> 01:10:37,400
Have you heard from Deb?

1201
01:10:37,440 --> 01:10:38,900
No.

1202
01:10:40,800 --> 01:10:42,700
Alex Stanson said he loves me.

1203
01:10:44,400 --> 01:10:47,900
I don't know what to do.

1204
01:10:49,500 --> 01:10:54,600
I have this invitation here for Nola
to Belinda Apple's book launch.

1205
01:10:55,800 --> 01:10:59,200
This is a letter from a woman in Duluth

1206
01:10:59,800 --> 01:11:03,000
telling Belinda that she saved her life.

1207
01:11:03,900 --> 01:11:07,400
Alex wants me, Nola,
to go to the book launch with him.

1208
01:11:07,440 --> 01:11:09,600
This woman needs Belinda to show up.

1209
01:11:10,600 --> 01:11:13,700
I can't be both people at the same time.

1210
01:11:14,600 --> 01:11:16,700
Rewind.
He said he loves you?

1211
01:11:16,740 --> 01:11:18,400
Yeah!

1212
01:11:18,440 --> 01:11:19,200
Wow.

1213
01:11:19,240 --> 01:11:20,500
And it's killing me.

1214
01:11:23,000 --> 01:11:26,800
I just... should have listened!
You were right.

1215
01:11:27,300 --> 01:11:28,800
You know, why did I make all this stuff up?

1216
01:11:28,840 --> 01:11:32,600
I should have just believed in myself
enough to tell Lori the truth from the beginning, and...

1217
01:11:32,640 --> 01:11:33,700
That is disgusting.

1218
01:11:33,740 --> 01:11:36,100
Well, a little simplistic, maybe, but...

1219
01:11:38,600 --> 01:11:41,900
For years, I have been hiding myself
under a homemade fat suit

1220
01:11:41,940 --> 01:11:43,700
so you wouldn't treat me
like a sex object,

1221
01:11:43,740 --> 01:11:47,600
and then I started shrinking
my body and building my self-esteem.

1222
01:11:47,640 --> 01:11:50,500
I even started to think
"maybe Ted's not so bad".

1223
01:11:50,540 --> 01:11:52,400
Maybe I was just imagining things

1224
